column2: # Calculating MSE for MLR models
PKW_mlr_mse <- mean((PKW_original_sample_prediction-PKW)^2)
SNFZ_mlr_mse <- mean((SNFZ_original_sample_prediction-SNFZ)^2)
LNFZ_mlr_mse <- mean((LNFZ_original_sample_prediction-LNFZ)^2)
KRAD_mlr_mse <- mean((KRAD_original_sample_prediction-KRAD)^2)
# Calculating MSE for Ridge models
PKW_ridge_mse <- mean((predict(PKW_fit, train, s = PKW_opt_lambda) %>% as.matrix() - PKW)^2)
SNFZ_ridge_mse <- mean((predict(SNFZ_fit, train, s = SNFZ_opt_lambda) %>% as.matrix() - SNFZ)^2)
LNFZ_ridge_mse <- mean((predict(LNFZ_fit, train, s = LNFZ_opt_lambda) %>% as.matrix() - LNFZ)^2)
KRAD_ridge_mse <- mean((predict(KRAD_fit, train, s = KRAD_opt_lambda) - KRAD)^2)
# Double checking MSE calculations (using ridge model, set lambda to 0)
PKW_ridge_mse_0 <- mean((predict(PKW_fit, train, s = 0) %>% as.matrix() - PKW)^2)
SNFZ_ridge_mse_0 <- mean((predict(SNFZ_fit, train, s = 0) %>% as.matrix() - SNFZ)^2)
LNFZ_ridge_mse_0 <- mean((predict(LNFZ_fit, train, s = 0) %>% as.matrix() - LNFZ)^2)
KRAD_ridge_mse_0 <- mean((predict(KRAD_fit, train, s = 0) - KRAD)^2)
print("MSE for PKW Ridge model on training data is:", quote = FALSE)
